				<table width="100%" cellspacing="5">
				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">The distinction I've usually heard made between simulation and emulation is whether one is simulating the physics/math of the original thing or instead executing a description of its function. Which leaves a lot of muddy room in the middle. <br /><br />Alternatively, simulation is a bottom-up description, whereas emulation is top-down.<br /><br />Ultimately, I don't think this point of pedantry exists outside of the groups that create and use emulators for hardware.</div>

					<br clear="all" /><br />

